// Conformance case: Stable "String/byte literal escape syntax"
// (STABILITY.md § Feature Stability › Stable). Complements
// `string_escapes.rz` with the empty-string literal, an escape as the
// very first character of a `println` argument (no leading text), a
// literal backslash immediately followed by a decoded escape, and
// `len()` on a string containing every shared escape in one literal.
fn main() {
    println("");
    println("just backslash: \\");
    println("mixed: \n\t\\\"end");
    println("no escapes here");
    let s = "a\nb\tc\\d\"e";
    println(len(s));
    println("tab\tthen\ttab");
}
main();
